Study
requests = guaranteed (scheduling), limits = max (enforced by kernel).
QoS classes: Guaranteed (req==limit), Burstable (req<limit), BestEffort (none).
CPU is compressible (throttle), memory is not (OOMKill).

Hands-On
resources:
  requests: {cpu: "100m", memory: "128Mi"}
  limits:   {cpu: "200m", memory: "256Mi"}

Run a memory hog: stress --vm 1 --vm-bytes 300M → observe OOMKilled in kubectl describe.
Run a CPU hog → observe throttling via kubectl top pod.

